WEBVTT

00:37.368 --> 00:39.706
♪

00:48.784 --> 00:53.784
Subtitles by explosiveskull

00:53.786 --> 00:54.820
[gasps]

01:24.917 --> 01:27.853
[music playing throughout]

01:36.227 --> 01:38.564
[birds cawing]

02:01.719 --> 02:04.257
♪

04:04.575 --> 04:05.677
[hearse engine revs]

04:21.427 --> 04:22.528
[honking]

04:30.468 --> 04:32.038
[gate rattles]

05:07.805 --> 05:09.341
[door whines]

05:11.610 --> 05:13.612
[tray screeches]

05:23.988 --> 05:25.889
Are you going
to stand out there,

05:25.891 --> 05:27.826
like a Statue of Liberty?

05:32.430 --> 05:34.897
Come on, I need your help.
I need a hand.

05:34.899 --> 05:36.435
Quick.

05:39.637 --> 05:41.373
[gate rattles]

05:55.821 --> 05:57.590
[gate slams shut]

06:08.867 --> 06:11.104
Not too close, okay?
He may bite you.

06:14.706 --> 06:17.873
Welcome
to my paradise, huh?

06:17.875 --> 06:20.110
Yes, oh, your... [chuckles]

06:20.112 --> 06:21.844
I'm so sorry
about your family.

06:21.846 --> 06:23.747
I cannot help you
with ninjas or karate.

06:23.749 --> 06:25.115
But guess what?
You know what?

06:25.117 --> 06:28.118
I can give you a job.
Come on, help me with this.

06:28.120 --> 06:30.620
Come on.

06:30.622 --> 06:33.123
Slowly, slowly,
slowly. Slowly!

06:33.125 --> 06:36.560
[water dripping]

06:36.562 --> 06:38.497
♪

07:27.713 --> 07:31.551
Don't worry, ninja man,
you are safe here.

07:42.995 --> 07:45.628
You will now meet my friend,

07:45.630 --> 07:47.596
Mr. Lester Green,

07:47.598 --> 07:50.966
a victim of robbery
in grocery store.

07:50.968 --> 07:53.235
He took bullet for his wife.

07:53.237 --> 07:54.870
He saved his wife.

07:54.872 --> 07:57.707
And I have to give him
beautiful face.

07:57.709 --> 08:02.178
I cannot send him
to paradise as a monster. No!

08:02.180 --> 08:05.848
I have to change this. I have
to give him beautiful face.

08:05.850 --> 08:07.584
Yeah, I will do that.

08:07.586 --> 08:11.053
The face of Cary Grant
or James Dean.

08:11.055 --> 08:13.656
That's what he needs.

08:13.658 --> 08:14.890
What do you think?

08:14.892 --> 08:17.159
Hmm?

08:17.161 --> 08:19.062
- Yes?
- Mm-hmm.

08:19.064 --> 08:20.596
Don't be scared, ninja man.

08:20.598 --> 08:24.000
I need your help.
Pass me the-the middle one.

08:24.002 --> 08:26.769
Yes. Come on.

08:26.771 --> 08:28.608
Come on.

08:32.878 --> 08:36.979
[grunts]

08:36.981 --> 08:39.148
Pass me this little dish
there. Come on.

08:39.150 --> 08:41.917
Yes. Right here.

08:41.919 --> 08:42.919
[tooth clatters]

08:42.921 --> 08:44.056
Okay.

08:48.961 --> 08:51.264
Please put this back.

08:53.698 --> 08:56.967
We love you, Mr. Lester.

08:56.969 --> 08:58.734
When you arrive in paradise,

08:58.736 --> 09:01.070
please send us
a little message.

09:01.072 --> 09:02.772
A little message.

09:02.774 --> 09:04.243
[teeth rattling]

09:10.682 --> 09:11.982
You like the gold?

09:11.984 --> 09:15.884
Yeah, it's beautiful, is it?
It's real pure gold.

09:15.886 --> 09:18.153
I collect all
these human pieces.

09:18.155 --> 09:19.989
And then, guess what?
Every six months,

09:19.991 --> 09:23.859
company show up, pick up,
and-and it's a tragedy,

09:23.861 --> 09:25.094
because they throw away.

09:25.096 --> 09:27.631
But guess what?
I have a little secret.

09:27.633 --> 09:29.866
Yeah, I do.

09:29.868 --> 09:32.736
I have some stashed
too as well, so...

09:32.738 --> 09:35.037
Yeah. But anyway, put this away.
Come on.

09:35.039 --> 09:37.208
We have to go back to work.
Come on.

09:39.344 --> 09:40.776
[tooth clatters]

09:40.778 --> 09:43.115
[vocalizing eerily]

09:48.754 --> 09:50.887
Close your eyes.

09:50.889 --> 09:52.991
It doesn't work when you
don't close your eyes.

09:54.826 --> 09:57.163
[vocalizing resumes]

10:03.134 --> 10:06.335
Mind, body, spirit.

10:06.337 --> 10:11.041
I give you face of Jesus,
King of Man.

10:11.043 --> 10:13.379
♪

10:48.813 --> 10:50.012
What do you think
about that?

10:50.014 --> 10:53.816
Looks good, huh?
Here you go. Wow.

10:53.818 --> 10:54.917
Look.

10:54.919 --> 10:58.220
I see you every day on the
bridge, and with big sign,

10:58.222 --> 10:59.488
and then I-I...

10:59.490 --> 11:01.223
You know, to be honest
with you, I'm sorry.

11:01.225 --> 11:05.427
I'm sorry for you. It makes
me so sad, you know?

11:05.429 --> 11:07.830
Guess what?
I give you work today.

11:07.832 --> 11:09.431
What about
a little work tonight?

11:09.433 --> 11:11.334
I pay you, and you have
a little money

11:11.336 --> 11:13.368
for a little cocoa
or something hot.

11:13.370 --> 11:15.939
Yes? Okay,
I know you're mute.

11:15.941 --> 11:17.343
It's okay,
don't worry about it.

11:18.844 --> 11:21.844
We have to move
three more bodies, okay?

11:21.846 --> 11:23.479
The next one
is very brutal.

11:23.481 --> 11:25.482
Oh, man! Somebody
push him from tree.

11:25.484 --> 11:28.251
He's a... he's a midget,
tiny little thing.

11:28.253 --> 11:31.087
We have to do something special
for him for funeral, okay?

11:31.089 --> 11:35.224
He can be Marlon Brando
or Tupac Shakur.

11:35.226 --> 11:38.194
Or something different.
We'll see. Okay?

11:38.196 --> 11:42.065
See, I have to create
something here. Yes?

11:42.067 --> 11:44.233
I know tomorrow
you'll be talking.

11:44.235 --> 11:46.335
I know that already.

11:46.337 --> 11:48.873
♪

12:02.553 --> 12:04.089
[zipping bag close]

12:24.241 --> 12:28.511
Hey. You have bloody t-shirt.
Take this one.

12:28.513 --> 12:32.415
I brought you also a beanie and jacket.
Here you go.

12:32.417 --> 12:34.950
Clean up yourself, you
look like homeless person.

12:34.952 --> 12:36.288
Come on.

12:42.427 --> 12:44.093
Let me give you pay here.

12:44.095 --> 12:46.595
You earn it.
Here.

12:46.597 --> 12:49.431
Do you need a ride home?

12:49.433 --> 12:51.834
Do you have a place to stay?

12:51.836 --> 12:55.371
How is your family? Huh?

12:55.373 --> 12:57.406
Okay, have a nice one.

12:57.408 --> 13:00.108
[Nice Legs' "Holy Night"
playing]

13:00.110 --> 13:05.080
<i>♪ I've made a few mistakes ♪</i>

13:05.082 --> 13:09.219
<i>♪ This year ♪</i>

13:09.221 --> 13:14.190
<i>♪ Meet me, please ♪</i>

13:14.192 --> 13:19.061
<i>♪ Where the lights are bright ♪</i>

13:19.063 --> 13:22.931
<i>♪ I'll make things right ♪</i>

13:22.933 --> 13:27.570
<i>♪ I've been bad ♪</i>

13:27.572 --> 13:31.543
<i>♪ I've got a good excuse ♪</i>

13:36.648 --> 13:41.316
<i>♪ I don't think ♪</i>

13:41.318 --> 13:46.222
<i>♪ You think of me at all ♪</i>

13:46.224 --> 13:50.225
<i>♪ But Christmas I'll be there ♪</i>

13:50.227 --> 13:55.031
<i>♪ I've been bad ♪</i>

13:55.033 --> 13:59.238
<i>♪ I've got a good excuse ♪</i>

14:03.975 --> 14:09.078
<i>♪ Meet me there ♪</i>

14:09.080 --> 14:13.949
<i>♪ Underneath the tree ♪</i>

14:13.951 --> 14:19.656
<i>♪ We'll find
our memories there ♪</i>

14:19.658 --> 14:22.193
♪

14:27.465 --> 14:33.504
<i>♪ We'll find
our memories there. ♪</i>

14:59.496 --> 15:02.367
Gold? I heard it's going up.

15:07.371 --> 15:10.074
I sold mine!
[laughs]

15:11.509 --> 15:13.211
[continues laughing]

15:33.063 --> 15:35.500
[papers rustle]

15:46.378 --> 15:48.714
♪

16:05.764 --> 16:08.567
[clears throat, coughs]

16:12.803 --> 16:17.140
<i>Hello... hello.</i>

16:17.142 --> 16:20.243
He-he-hello.

16:20.245 --> 16:21.545
Hi.

16:21.547 --> 16:24.079
<i>Hey, hey, it's me from the...
from the other night.</i>

16:24.081 --> 16:25.781
<i>I... I forgot...</i>

16:25.783 --> 16:28.253
I forgot my-my bag. Um...

16:30.455 --> 16:31.653
My black... my little bag.

16:31.655 --> 16:35.157
It's a black thing.
And, uh...

16:35.159 --> 16:36.725
and then maybe I can...

16:36.727 --> 16:39.094
Can I... I can...
can I help you? I...

16:39.096 --> 16:41.531
Can you help...
Can you give me a job?

16:41.533 --> 16:45.501
<i>I'm not dangerous.
I-I'm just... I...</i>

16:45.503 --> 16:48.570
I'm just hopeless
at this-at this time.

16:48.572 --> 16:51.273
<i>If you just let me help you, I'll
work for an hour. I'll work for free.</i>

16:51.275 --> 16:53.276
<i>And if you don't like
what I do,</i>

16:53.278 --> 16:55.811
I'll get the hell out
and I'll fucking split.

16:55.813 --> 16:59.581
But if you do like it, maybe
you can give me a little job.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.486
Like you say, right?

17:10.260 --> 17:15.134
Oh, Marisa...
It's all in the past.

17:17.602 --> 17:19.238
We got this.

17:21.439 --> 17:23.108
[inhales deeply]

17:34.384 --> 17:36.721
[dog barking]

17:43.127 --> 17:45.760
- Whoa!
- [trash clatters]

17:45.762 --> 17:48.331
You cannot break me. You
cannot break me. Okay?

17:48.333 --> 17:50.232
- Who are you?!
- It's me, from the other night.

17:50.234 --> 17:50.232
From the other night.
The... the...

17:50.234 --> 17:52.701
Remember?

17:52.703 --> 17:54.903
- Ninja. Ninja man.
- Yeah. Yeah.

17:54.905 --> 17:58.207
You can talk.
You can talk.

17:58.209 --> 18:01.309
So where is your beard?
What happened to your beard?

18:01.311 --> 18:03.645
You don't have it. You shave it.
You look better.

18:03.647 --> 18:06.449
So what brings you
here to my office?

18:06.451 --> 18:08.316
Well, I forgot
my-my bag.

18:08.318 --> 18:10.786
- What color?
- It's black. Small bag.

18:10.788 --> 18:12.921
- Black? Are you sure it's black?
- Yeah, it's black.

18:12.923 --> 18:14.289
Yeah, it's black.

18:14.291 --> 18:16.691
You know what?
Maybe it was this one?

18:16.693 --> 18:19.428
- No, that's not it.
- No. No.

18:19.430 --> 18:22.565
[rustling]

18:22.567 --> 18:24.834
- Is this it?
- Yeah.

18:24.836 --> 18:26.637
Here you go.

18:35.846 --> 18:38.881
[stammering]
Um, I-I-I need help.

18:38.883 --> 18:41.918
- What kind of help?
- Can you help me? Can I work for you?

18:41.920 --> 18:43.818
What kind of qualification
skills do you have?

18:43.820 --> 18:45.787
- Well, I do...
- Communication, I meant.

18:45.789 --> 18:49.592
I worked as a janitor. I can...
I can clean. You know?

18:49.594 --> 18:51.861
- I can stack stuff for you.
- Everybody can clean.

18:51.863 --> 18:54.630
- I see these coffins.
- I don't think so.

18:54.632 --> 18:56.632
- No, I can help you.
- I don't think so.

18:56.634 --> 18:59.669
- I can bring the trash out.
- You know what? I give you advice.

18:59.671 --> 19:03.338
- Go back to school.
- I don't... I don't need school.

19:03.340 --> 19:06.241
School is not what I'm looking for.
I need a job. I need help.

19:06.243 --> 19:08.311
Let me help you.
I'll work for free.

19:08.313 --> 19:10.746
You help me or you want
me to help you?

19:10.748 --> 19:12.914
I can help you clean. I can
help you organize your office.

19:12.916 --> 19:15.218
- So you need my help?
- I need a job.

19:15.220 --> 19:16.885
- Yes or no?
- I need a job.

19:16.887 --> 19:18.787
- Do you need my help, yes or no?
- Yes. I need a job.

19:18.789 --> 19:19.788
So why you hesitate?

19:19.790 --> 19:21.891
I need your help.

19:21.893 --> 19:24.594
Just give me an hour
and I'll work for free.

19:24.596 --> 19:25.530
Okay, follow me.

19:35.506 --> 19:37.442
[spraying noises]

19:38.643 --> 19:41.180
♪

20:23.387 --> 20:24.855
[rattling]

20:52.884 --> 20:54.419
[contents rattle]

20:59.057 --> 21:00.759
Ninja man?

21:07.999 --> 21:09.931
Come on, where are you?

21:09.933 --> 21:11.470
Hey! Ninja man!

21:36.461 --> 21:38.396
- [gasps in disbelief]
- [bag thuds]

21:41.699 --> 21:46.901
[muffled] I made it last night.
Just for fun.

21:46.903 --> 21:48.504
Can I have it?

21:48.506 --> 21:49.807
Sure.

21:53.411 --> 21:56.144
Sure you can have it.

21:56.146 --> 21:58.713
[chuckles] It's you!

21:58.715 --> 21:59.950
Here you go.

22:02.987 --> 22:04.487
You are a guest here.

22:04.489 --> 22:06.389
You have special access.

22:06.391 --> 22:09.124
You can have it,
it's a gift for you.

22:09.126 --> 22:12.026
I can't believe it, this is...
you're an incredible artist.

22:12.028 --> 22:14.963
But you know,
I'm sad tonight.

22:14.965 --> 22:19.602
Mr. Lee is gone to paradise.

22:19.604 --> 22:24.006
You know what we should do? We should
have Chinese food in his honor.

22:24.008 --> 22:26.040
Yeah.

22:26.042 --> 22:29.044
He was very kind, kind,
you know, Chinese man,

22:29.046 --> 22:31.146
Can you imagine?

22:31.148 --> 22:33.649
Chinese usually are
very selfish, you know?

22:33.651 --> 22:36.117
But who cares?
He was special.

22:36.119 --> 22:40.189
Very special guy.
Very special Chinese person.

22:40.191 --> 22:43.491
Let's have Chinese food.

22:43.493 --> 22:45.527
♪

22:45.529 --> 22:47.496
[Harvey]
<i>♪ Cheers to Mr. Lee ♪</i>

22:47.498 --> 22:50.466
<i>♪ And my new friend,
Ninja Man. ♪</i>

22:50.468 --> 22:52.434
<i>♪ Ninja Man ♪</i>

22:52.436 --> 22:54.469
<i>♪ Cheers to Mr. Lee ♪</i>

22:54.471 --> 22:55.671
Cheers, hey!

22:55.673 --> 22:58.073
- Cheers. Yeah.
- Yeah, Mr. Lee.

22:58.075 --> 23:00.042
Yeah. Sorry.

23:00.044 --> 23:02.644
- [paper rustles]
- [Ninja Man] Ahem.

23:02.646 --> 23:07.650
So tell me, what-what-
what is your real name?

23:07.652 --> 23:09.084
Is it big secret
or something?

23:09.086 --> 23:11.821
- You cannot tell me?
- Oh, Jon.

23:11.823 --> 23:13.521
- Jon!
- Jon is my real name.

23:13.523 --> 23:16.659
Jon! [laughs]
This is ordinary name.

23:16.661 --> 23:21.063
Pretty nice. Pretty nice.

23:21.065 --> 23:22.864
What are you...
You're a doctor?

23:22.866 --> 23:27.068
No, I hate doctors.
I'm a specialist.

23:27.070 --> 23:30.805
I help people. My goal
is to make people happy,

23:30.807 --> 23:32.941
especially when they die.

23:32.943 --> 23:37.813
I give them new faces.
I'm still in business.

23:37.815 --> 23:40.915
Who is this woman?
She's beautiful.

23:40.917 --> 23:43.919
Long, long time ago,
they find her in the park.

23:43.921 --> 23:48.724
Two different pieces.
And... it was a tragedy.

23:48.726 --> 23:52.061
She used to want to be
a big star.

23:52.063 --> 23:55.498
She won a beauty pageant.

23:55.500 --> 23:57.600
They never find
the killer.

23:57.602 --> 23:59.971
Elizabeth was a big tragedy.

24:06.109 --> 24:07.977
<i>You know what?
I want to cry.</i>

24:07.979 --> 24:11.917
Each time I think about it,
I want to cry about it.

24:14.551 --> 24:16.086
Where did this happen?

24:18.154 --> 24:19.555
It was a tragedy
in Los Angeles.

24:19.557 --> 24:23.758
- <i>Why are you asking this question?</i>
- <i>[sighs]</i>

24:23.760 --> 24:26.629
- It was a long time ago.
- So is this...

24:26.631 --> 24:28.296
Is this what inspired
all this? The face masks?

24:28.298 --> 24:32.234
No, no, not at all.
I inspire myself.

24:32.236 --> 24:33.635
Okay.

24:33.637 --> 24:38.306
I make people happy.
That's my goal in life.

24:38.308 --> 24:42.076
You know, corporate
try to close me down,

24:42.078 --> 24:46.183
but people understand that
I do something good here.

24:49.619 --> 24:52.654
So, hey, Jon,
what's your real job?

24:52.656 --> 24:55.958
I mean, look at you. I see always your bag.
Is your bag there?

24:55.960 --> 24:58.727
Oh, yeah, it's right there,
next to you.

24:58.729 --> 25:00.228
Are you working
in a parking lot?

25:00.230 --> 25:01.997
Or selling drugs?

25:01.999 --> 25:04.967
Or maybe a little prostitution
on the street, huh? Mm?

25:04.969 --> 25:09.037
- What do you do?
- Oh, I'm... I'm kinda new in town.

25:09.039 --> 25:12.106
- Just feeling it out.
- Oh, you are a drifter?

25:12.108 --> 25:15.044
- Wow! A drifter?
- Yeah, well...

25:15.046 --> 25:16.644
In and out. In and out, huh?

25:16.646 --> 25:19.047
Yeah, well,
I worked in the Army.

25:19.049 --> 25:20.216
Well, how was it?

25:20.218 --> 25:25.054
Army? I don't know. I was
hoping to find some direction,

25:25.056 --> 25:27.855
- and make friends, but it didn't work out.
- And what happened?

25:27.857 --> 25:29.924
It just didn't work out.

25:29.926 --> 25:34.630
So what do you
want to be? Hm?

25:34.632 --> 25:39.367
<i>♪ What do you want
to be, Jon? ♪</i>

25:39.369 --> 25:41.636
- Mm?
- Um, I... I...

25:41.638 --> 25:43.838
I guess I hope to be me.

25:43.840 --> 25:47.142
♪

25:47.144 --> 25:50.345
I see your eyes.
Your eyes so sad, Jon.

25:50.347 --> 25:55.284
What do you worry about? We have
Chinese food. We celebrate. We live.

25:55.286 --> 25:57.987
Why don't you live,
Jon?! Live!

25:57.989 --> 26:02.027
<i>♪ Live, live, live, live! ♪</i>

26:04.127 --> 26:08.263
I'm not pushing you, but you can
stay here if you like. You know?

26:08.265 --> 26:10.199
- [stammers] I... um...
- Oh, do you...

26:10.201 --> 26:14.169
I know some people on the east side.
I have a place.

26:14.171 --> 26:18.907
[stammering] Do you... Do you
need a ride or something?

26:18.909 --> 26:20.942
I'm-I'm okay.

26:20.944 --> 26:23.314
♪

27:57.007 --> 27:59.344
♪

28:06.916 --> 28:09.253
[printer whirring]

28:16.493 --> 28:19.029
[train rattling]

28:38.782 --> 28:41.118
[music playing over speakers]

28:55.532 --> 28:57.501
[woman] Jon?

29:03.574 --> 29:06.111
♪

29:18.888 --> 29:21.225
[hissing]

29:30.000 --> 29:32.534
Dr Surtain.

29:32.536 --> 29:35.304
You look
pretty banged up.

29:35.306 --> 29:37.040
What can I
help you with?

29:55.291 --> 29:57.227
[music playing]

30:34.498 --> 30:36.163
[Harvey]
<i>Can you lift harder?</i>

30:36.165 --> 30:40.035
I mean, all my weight
is right here, not there.

30:40.037 --> 30:42.069
Just go straight.
Straight, straight, straight.

30:42.071 --> 30:44.139
Watch what you are doing.
What are you...?

30:44.141 --> 30:46.440
- [coffin thuds]
- Shit, damn it!

30:46.442 --> 30:48.576
Sammy Jr.,
I'm so sorry!

30:48.578 --> 30:52.280
Baby, I'm sorry!
I'm sorry.

30:52.282 --> 30:53.382
What did you do to him?

30:53.384 --> 30:56.951
- [train crossing bell ringing]
- Now he cannot sleep.

30:56.953 --> 30:59.220
Just get your side.
Get the other side.

30:59.222 --> 31:01.923
- Don't talk to me like that, man.
- Hold on, just balance it.

31:01.925 --> 31:03.057
[both grunting]

31:03.059 --> 31:04.927
Up... Up!

31:04.929 --> 31:05.964
[groans]

31:08.999 --> 31:10.367
Go straight. Straight.

31:11.434 --> 31:14.102
[grunting with effort]

31:14.104 --> 31:17.238
Oh! I cannot do this
anymore.

31:17.240 --> 31:18.442
Ah, man.

31:19.509 --> 31:21.144
Come on.

31:27.718 --> 31:30.017
Do you have a girl
or something?

31:30.019 --> 31:33.689
Nah, I'm just...
just doing my own thing.

31:33.691 --> 31:35.590
But how about you?
Do you have a family?

31:35.592 --> 31:37.025
[sighs]

31:37.027 --> 31:39.428
Not at this time.

31:39.430 --> 31:42.363
You know...

31:42.365 --> 31:45.132
loneliness
is hard sometimes,

31:45.134 --> 31:47.469
but it's easier
than losing someone.

31:47.471 --> 31:49.106
Do you understand?

31:51.642 --> 31:54.075
You know, I was thinking...

31:54.077 --> 31:56.010
maybe we could hang out
sometime.

31:56.012 --> 31:58.246
You know, outside
of this place.

31:58.248 --> 32:02.017
Right? Like friends.

32:02.019 --> 32:04.385
Well, I have news
for you.[chuckles]

32:04.387 --> 32:06.755
Once a year,
I go to Vegas.

32:06.757 --> 32:08.356
Open road.

32:08.358 --> 32:10.659
Golden Nugget.

32:10.661 --> 32:14.129
Forget the world, man.
Have groovy time.

32:14.131 --> 32:17.532
- Spend some moolah. You want to go?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah!

32:17.534 --> 32:21.169
- When are you thinking?
- Um... tonight!

32:21.171 --> 32:23.705
- Tonight?
- Yeah!

32:23.707 --> 32:26.341
- All right, yeah, let's do it.
- Let's do it, man.

32:26.343 --> 32:28.642
- How are we going to get there?
- By car, what do you think?

32:28.644 --> 32:30.511
- All right.
- You don't have to pay for anything.

32:30.513 --> 32:35.116
- [chuckles] Yeah. Let's go. I'm ready.
- Okay, let's go.

32:35.118 --> 32:37.454
♪

32:53.069 --> 32:54.004
Yeah!

33:14.557 --> 33:16.326
[Jon chuckling]

33:44.688 --> 33:47.225
[music playing]

35:03.766 --> 35:05.535
[crickets chirping]

35:11.541 --> 35:13.441
[Jon] Oh, I love the book
<i>Of Mice and Men.</i>

35:13.443 --> 35:14.508
Have you read
that book?

35:14.510 --> 35:16.211
- Yeah, friendship.
- Yeah?

35:16.213 --> 35:17.845
I always...
I don't know,

35:17.847 --> 35:19.813
I always saw myself in Lenny
and George, you know,

35:19.815 --> 35:22.316
these two people just...

35:22.318 --> 35:23.918
wanting to live
off the fat of the land

35:23.920 --> 35:25.854
and have a place
to call home.

35:25.856 --> 35:27.458
Yeah.

35:29.393 --> 35:34.862
- The feeling is friendship, huh?
- Mm. Yeah.

35:34.864 --> 35:37.499
You know, this is the... this is
the first time I've felt alive

35:37.501 --> 35:39.300
in a long time, and...

35:39.302 --> 35:41.802
you know, I almost forgot
what it felt like.

35:41.804 --> 35:45.773
- It's all thanks to you.
- Mm.

35:45.775 --> 35:49.311
Guess what?

35:49.313 --> 35:52.646
Do you want to be
my partner? Business partner?

35:52.648 --> 35:55.749
- What? Business partner?
- Yeah, business partner.

35:55.751 --> 35:59.387
I can give you keys
and you can go in and out.

35:59.389 --> 36:00.655
I-I would love that.

36:00.657 --> 36:02.324
- Mm.
- Yeah.

36:02.326 --> 36:04.892
- Yes? Give me five.
- Yeah! Yeah.

36:04.894 --> 36:05.927
[grunting with effort]

36:05.929 --> 36:07.896
- Do it again.
- Yeah. [groans]

36:07.898 --> 36:09.331
You're a little clumsy today.

36:09.333 --> 36:10.798
Yeah. Oh, it's cold.

36:10.800 --> 36:13.834
- [Harvey] Oh.
- It's cold.

36:13.836 --> 36:15.836
- Look at the stars.
- Being out here

36:15.838 --> 36:20.608
just reminds me of my mom,
you know, before...

36:20.610 --> 36:23.411
- before she died. She would...
- She died?!

36:23.413 --> 36:26.615
- <i>When?</i>
- <i>Oh, years ago.</i>

36:26.617 --> 36:28.583
Well, you say
like it's recent.

36:28.585 --> 36:31.318
- <i>No, it was years ago, but...</i>
- <i>Sorry about that.</i>

36:31.320 --> 36:33.657
♪

36:43.967 --> 36:45.800
Yeah, just when I look up,

36:45.802 --> 36:48.403
I think about, like,
she would take me...

36:48.405 --> 36:50.972
she'd take me
to the Observatory,

36:50.974 --> 36:52.840
<i>and... I don't know...</i>

36:52.842 --> 36:56.010
<i>Like, she would always want
to get me involved in nature.</i>

36:56.012 --> 36:58.215
[exhales sharply]

36:59.782 --> 37:02.252
♪

37:24.641 --> 37:26.541
<i>I promised her
that I wouldn't end up</i>

37:26.543 --> 37:30.744
- like my father.
- Promise what?

37:30.746 --> 37:32.613
She wanted me
to finish college,

37:32.615 --> 37:35.316
and I... I totally
dropped the ball.

37:35.318 --> 37:38.320
- <i>Yeah.</i>
- <i>I haven't made good on anything, and...</i>

37:38.322 --> 37:41.488
you know, my dad, he was a
bum, you know? And he...

37:41.490 --> 37:43.791
<i>he lost our house
and he disappeared.</i>

37:43.793 --> 37:47.996
And I've just been... I've just
been bouncing around ever since.

37:47.998 --> 37:49.396
Hey, don't wo...
Listen.

37:49.398 --> 37:51.398
Don't worry about it.
She's up there, look!

37:51.400 --> 37:52.633
In the sky!

37:52.635 --> 37:54.969
<i>♪ Hello! Hello! ♪</i>

37:54.971 --> 37:56.905
<i>♪ Your son is here ♪</i>

37:56.907 --> 37:59.507
<i>♪ Hello! Hello! ♪</i>

37:59.509 --> 38:00.641
She's very proud of you.

38:00.643 --> 38:03.445
She's out there.
You see?

38:03.447 --> 38:05.282
She's very proud
of you, Jon.

38:06.550 --> 38:08.983
<i>Very proud of you.</i>

38:08.985 --> 38:13.454
Hello? Your son is right here, yes.
You see?

38:13.456 --> 38:17.458
You don't want to say hey?
Hello. Hi, hi, hi.

38:17.460 --> 38:20.363
She's proud of you, yes.

38:22.898 --> 38:24.402
She's proud of you.

38:25.969 --> 38:27.769
- You think?
- Yes.

38:27.771 --> 38:30.574
- How would you know?
- I can feel.

38:32.608 --> 38:33.677
[fuse crackling]

38:37.514 --> 38:39.849
♪

39:04.775 --> 39:07.508
Are we ready to go?

39:07.510 --> 39:10.614
[Jon] <i>Yeah, I think I'm
finally ready to go back.</i>

39:43.012 --> 39:47.449
<i>"Harvey, I want to tell you
about something that I did.</i>

39:47.451 --> 39:48.717
<i>The week before Vegas,</i>

39:48.719 --> 39:50.985
<i>I stole two bags of gold teeth
from your storage room</i>

39:50.987 --> 39:52.586
<i>and I sold them for money.</i>

39:52.588 --> 39:55.690
<i>I feel awful about it and I
didn't know how to tell you."</i>

39:55.692 --> 39:58.559
♪

39:58.561 --> 40:01.128
<i>"But the good news is,
I think I found something,</i>

40:01.130 --> 40:02.930
<i>something that can help
both of us</i>

40:02.932 --> 40:04.835
<i>and I want to bring you
in on it."</i>

40:08.538 --> 40:11.539
<i>"Your friend, Jon."</i>

40:11.541 --> 40:13.878
♪

40:59.822 --> 41:03.758
So, I hate to be the one
to break it to you,

41:03.760 --> 41:05.663
but we are closing up.

41:07.731 --> 41:08.963
Where are you from?

41:08.965 --> 41:12.700
Arizona. You?

41:12.702 --> 41:15.202
Um, complicated question,

41:15.204 --> 41:20.575
but I'd go with, uh,
Central-Central Cali.

41:20.577 --> 41:23.577
Complicated.
What's your name?

41:23.579 --> 41:25.112
Uh... Jon.

41:25.114 --> 41:27.882
Jon. Traci.

41:27.884 --> 41:29.583
Nice to...
nice to meet you.

41:29.585 --> 41:30.651
Likewise.

41:30.653 --> 41:33.253
So what are you doing
in L.A.?

41:33.255 --> 41:35.889
Um, I'm kind of in the...
in the gold business.

41:35.891 --> 41:38.626
"The gold business."
Okay, that's a new one.

41:38.628 --> 41:41.162
- [laughs]
- I never heard that before.

41:41.164 --> 41:42.697
It's kind of going well.

41:42.699 --> 41:44.001
- Good.
- Yeah. Um...

41:46.802 --> 41:47.737
Keep it.

41:51.775 --> 41:53.907
Well...

41:53.909 --> 41:55.809
my shift's up,

41:55.811 --> 42:00.782
so if you want to tell me
that long story, I got time.

42:00.784 --> 42:03.650
- Do you want to take a walk?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

42:03.652 --> 42:05.221
Sure. Yeah.

42:07.923 --> 42:10.260
♪

42:45.894 --> 42:49.097
Well, thanks
for walking me home.

42:49.099 --> 42:51.932
It was fun.
I had a nice time.

42:51.934 --> 42:52.936
You're interesting.

42:54.903 --> 42:58.005
- You want to get coffee?
- Right now?

42:58.007 --> 43:03.244
No, it's midnight!
I meant another time.

43:03.246 --> 43:05.880
I'd love that, yeah.

43:05.882 --> 43:07.184
[giggles] Okay.

43:15.992 --> 43:19.159
[door squeaks]

43:19.161 --> 43:21.264
- Good night.
- Night.

43:23.699 --> 43:26.035
♪

43:47.190 --> 43:50.391
Jon, is everything okay?

43:50.393 --> 43:51.726
Yeah.

43:51.728 --> 43:53.994
Well, you didn't show up
last night.

43:53.996 --> 43:55.762
Yeah, I was out late.

43:55.764 --> 43:57.398
Yeah, but the office
was not ready.

43:57.400 --> 43:59.333
And this morning... I
had to clean up today.

43:59.335 --> 44:02.970
Sorry, I... I just...
met a girl.

44:02.972 --> 44:05.173
A girl?

44:05.175 --> 44:07.340
Um, she's...
yeah, she's awesome.

44:07.342 --> 44:11.778
- Do you see the stars? Mm?
- Yeah.

44:11.780 --> 44:13.748
I'm happy for you.

44:13.750 --> 44:17.284
But look.
I rely on you.

44:17.286 --> 44:19.220
Okay? You have to show up
for work here, you know?

44:19.222 --> 44:20.822
I cannot do you work.

44:20.824 --> 44:22.724
It's not right,
is it? Huh?

44:22.726 --> 44:25.193
I apologize, it won't...
it won't happen again.

44:25.195 --> 44:27.729
Well, we have new order.

44:27.731 --> 44:30.231
A clown family. I need your
assistance right here.

44:30.233 --> 44:33.934
So the guy kill
himself. Okay?

44:33.936 --> 44:36.771
And by the way, they request
that you don't touch anything.

44:36.773 --> 44:39.977
Just let it go
until-until funeral, okay?

44:41.878 --> 44:44.715
You understand?
Don't touch anything.

44:46.282 --> 44:48.052
[sighs] Poor guy.

44:50.119 --> 44:52.452
If you look at the X-ray...
look it.

44:52.454 --> 44:53.621
- You see the candle?
- Mm-hmm.

44:53.623 --> 44:57.791
- He swallowed candle. He kill himself.
- How sad.

44:57.793 --> 45:00.461
And the second candle, put in his ass.
What about that?

45:00.463 --> 45:02.929
- [Jon] What? Oh, man!
- Yeah!

45:02.931 --> 45:05.099
[Harvey] This entire
family so weird.

45:05.101 --> 45:07.769
- Clown family? Wow!
- Clown family?

45:07.771 --> 45:11.005
- [Jon] All of them clowns?
- Yeah, they're weird like hell.

45:11.007 --> 45:12.273
You know,
we should celebrate.

45:12.275 --> 45:13.508
Like, eat, uh, cake,

45:13.510 --> 45:17.811
- Okay.
- Like, uh... sorbet, or...

45:17.813 --> 45:19.981
I'm going to finish
cleaning the coffins,

45:19.983 --> 45:22.516
and then let's do something
for clown man tomorrow night.

45:22.518 --> 45:23.918
Okay, clown man
tomorrow night.

45:23.920 --> 45:25.820
But guess what? I have
something for you.

45:25.822 --> 45:30.458
- Keys for entire place.
- Oh. Thank you!

45:30.460 --> 45:32.492
Okay, go to work!

45:32.494 --> 45:35.031
♪

45:43.873 --> 45:46.106
[Traci]
College was good, I mean...

45:46.108 --> 45:48.476
Something was just
kind of missing, so...

45:48.478 --> 45:52.412
I originally wanted to be in
Colorado, but I ended up here.

45:52.414 --> 45:53.981
What's in Colorado?

45:53.983 --> 45:57.050
Colorado? What's not in Colorado?
Are you kidding me?

45:57.052 --> 45:59.119
They have the most
majestic mountains

45:59.121 --> 46:00.121
you'll ever see.

46:00.123 --> 46:02.255
Freshest air
you'll ever breathe.

46:02.257 --> 46:04.291
The waterfalls
are incredible.

46:04.293 --> 46:08.429
- [chuckles] - And, like,
the whitest Christmases.

46:08.431 --> 46:09.930
Oh, my gosh!

46:09.932 --> 46:12.400
Have you ever had
a white Christmas?

46:12.402 --> 46:14.938
Well, no. I never have.

46:19.309 --> 46:21.845
♪

47:26.175 --> 47:28.309
[coin clatters]

47:28.311 --> 47:30.881
[line ringing]

47:36.085 --> 47:38.519
Andrei, hey,
this is Jon.

47:38.521 --> 47:40.423
Dr. Surtain gave me
your number.

47:41.690 --> 47:42.956
Yeah, I sold him
some dental scrap

47:42.958 --> 47:45.494
and he thought you might be
interested in, uh, in what I have.

47:47.496 --> 47:49.530
I have... I have tons.
I have bags...

47:49.532 --> 47:51.432
bags of, uh,
bags of stuff.

47:51.434 --> 47:52.402
A whole storage unit full.

47:54.536 --> 47:57.139
Well, my partner,
uh, he runs a morgue, so...

47:59.474 --> 48:01.978
Yeah, um...
Yeah, I can do tonight.

48:03.445 --> 48:05.412
It's over, uh,
it's over on the east side.

48:05.414 --> 48:07.516
It's, uh,
6200 Valley Boulevard.

48:10.085 --> 48:11.251
Yeah.

48:11.253 --> 48:12.521
How much?

48:14.523 --> 48:15.990
Yeah, yeah,
I'll be there.

48:15.992 --> 48:19.427
I'll be there. All right, I'll see you...
see you a little bit later.

48:19.429 --> 48:21.128
Okay.

48:21.130 --> 48:22.633
Yeah, no problem,
thank you.

48:29.438 --> 48:32.639
You can profit from it too, so I
didn't really steal from you.

48:32.641 --> 48:37.043
Uh... Oh, just say
the truth. [mumbles]

48:37.045 --> 48:42.182
Um, you know, I think...

48:42.184 --> 48:45.418
I think this could be something that
could help both of us, you know?

48:45.420 --> 48:49.490
Hey, Harvey, I want
to tell you something.

48:49.492 --> 48:53.094
[sighs]
This fucking sounds...

48:53.096 --> 48:57.597
Harvey, yeah, I want
to tell you something.

48:57.599 --> 48:59.566
Yeah, the week
before Vegas, um,

48:59.568 --> 49:04.637
you know, I kind of... I kind
of took something from you.

49:04.639 --> 49:09.043
Uh, yeah, I was going through
your-your storage and I fell down,

49:09.045 --> 49:10.577
and I saw these...

49:10.579 --> 49:14.081
Just be honest.
Just tell him the truth.

49:14.083 --> 49:16.420
♪

49:26.728 --> 49:28.497
[hearse door opens]

49:39.275 --> 49:44.045
Jon, I give you keys so you can
work like a partner, right?

49:44.047 --> 49:45.545
What are you doing here?

49:45.547 --> 49:47.514
You look like
a homeless person.

49:47.516 --> 49:49.251
Read this.

49:52.320 --> 49:56.293
- You became writer now?
- It'll explain everything.

50:11.440 --> 50:13.709
♪

50:14.777 --> 50:16.644
Is this real?

50:16.646 --> 50:20.313
I was desperate and I...
I made a mistake.

50:20.315 --> 50:23.550
Jon, you steal from me.
You steal from my friends.

50:23.552 --> 50:26.854
You sell body parts
on the black market.

50:26.856 --> 50:29.322
- Why you doing this? Why?
- Come on.

50:29.324 --> 50:31.124
Come on.
It's not like that.

50:31.126 --> 50:36.162
I found something, all right? It's
a legit industry. This thing...

50:36.164 --> 50:38.532
- It can help us.
- Legit, not legit.

50:38.534 --> 50:41.101
Yu know, I want you to just leave now.
Give me the keys back.

50:41.103 --> 50:42.436
Okay? I don't want
to work with you.

50:42.438 --> 50:44.237
Come on, I-I have
nowhere to go.

50:44.239 --> 50:46.474
Whose problem is it?
It's my problem?

50:46.476 --> 50:49.543
This can really help you.

50:49.545 --> 50:52.179
All right? You have a ton of dental
scrap sitting in your storage.

50:52.181 --> 50:54.414
And it's just
collecting dust.

50:54.416 --> 50:55.615
[sighs]

50:55.617 --> 50:58.452
I've been wanting to tell you
since we got back from Vegas,

50:58.454 --> 51:01.421
and I...
I haven't had a chance.

51:01.423 --> 51:03.190
You met the girl.
That's okay with me.

51:03.192 --> 51:04.592
Okay? But look
at yourself now.

51:04.594 --> 51:07.628
You look like a zombie.
Your eyes pop out.

51:07.630 --> 51:10.831
Okay? Mark my words.

51:10.833 --> 51:13.800
It will not end up
well for you, okay?

51:13.802 --> 51:15.105
Look.

51:22.612 --> 51:24.577
[mocking laugh]

51:24.579 --> 51:27.380
It doesn't look real, anyhow,
you know, for your information.

51:27.382 --> 51:29.249
But what to do with you?
You tell me.

51:29.251 --> 51:36.257
I have a contact, all right?
His name is Andrei.

51:36.259 --> 51:38.358
Now you invite criminals
to my office.

51:38.360 --> 51:41.327
No, he's not a criminal. He
runs the refinery. All right?

51:41.329 --> 51:43.396
He wants to come here and he
wants to look at your scrap.

51:43.398 --> 51:45.331
And if he likes it,
he'll buy everything

51:45.333 --> 51:46.867
and give you maybe
a lot of cash.

51:46.869 --> 51:48.001
How much?

51:48.003 --> 51:50.170
I don't know until he comes
here and looks at it.

51:50.172 --> 51:51.271
Today is not my day.

51:51.273 --> 51:53.574
You can make money off of this.
You can benefit.

51:53.576 --> 51:55.675
All right? Just, please.
All I'm asking you...

51:55.677 --> 51:58.311
just give it an hour.
Let him come here.

51:58.313 --> 52:00.780
Oh, Jon.

52:00.782 --> 52:03.416
You know what? All right,
all right, all right.

52:03.418 --> 52:06.887
We will have, uh, meeting,
okay? We see what happens.

52:06.889 --> 52:08.956
But Jon, when you
end up in jail,

52:08.958 --> 52:10.590
I will not
rescue you, okay?

52:10.592 --> 52:12.193
The only thing
what I can do,

52:12.195 --> 52:15.295
I can send you
few oranges.

52:15.297 --> 52:17.197
<i>Tu comprends la vie?</i>

52:17.199 --> 52:18.932
- You got that?
- I got it.

52:18.934 --> 52:21.237
- Here. Keep it.
- Thank you. Sorry.

52:22.905 --> 52:25.442
♪

52:29.277 --> 52:30.846
[doorbell buzzing]

52:36.918 --> 52:39.753
Who are you?

52:39.755 --> 52:41.889
Who are <i>you?</i>
Are you Jon?

52:41.891 --> 52:43.724
No, I'm not Jon.

52:43.726 --> 52:45.925
Wait a minute. Before you
enter into my paradise,

52:45.927 --> 52:48.829
I have to... I have to
check for little stuff.

52:48.831 --> 52:50.331
- Okay?
- Okay.

52:50.333 --> 52:51.632
Okay, let me see
what you have...

52:51.634 --> 52:53.266
Do you have a gun
or something on you?

52:53.268 --> 52:56.637
- No.
- Okay. What is in the bag?

52:56.639 --> 52:58.606
- Okay, green stuff. Great.
- Uh-huh.

52:58.608 --> 53:00.474
Okay, we talk
about this later.

53:00.476 --> 53:03.376
Ladies, I'm sorry, but I
have to check you too, okay?

53:03.378 --> 53:05.412
Does it look like I can
hide a gun in this dress?

53:05.414 --> 53:07.981
Look, you look innocent,
you look very innocent,

53:07.983 --> 53:10.650
but you may hide a gun
or something in your ass.

53:10.652 --> 53:12.820
- You never know. You never know.
- [scoffs] What?

53:12.822 --> 53:15.655
- Who is this guy?
- Okay, okay. You okay. Okay.

53:15.657 --> 53:17.490
- How are you?
- Are you serious? Me too?

53:17.492 --> 53:18.992
- Yeah, hold on a minute.
- [Andrei] Sorry.

53:18.994 --> 53:20.793
- Is this some type of joke?
- Yeah, you okay.

53:20.795 --> 53:23.265
You guys go forward.

53:27.637 --> 53:28.901
♪

53:28.903 --> 53:31.942
Welcome to my paradise.
After you, please.

53:36.978 --> 53:38.845
- You Jon, the guy I spoke to on the phone?
- Yeah.

53:38.847 --> 53:40.613
- Nice meeting you.
- Nice to meet you.

53:40.615 --> 53:42.483
So how do you know Surtain
and the boys?

53:42.485 --> 53:44.450
We sold them some stuff
and they really liked it.

53:44.452 --> 53:47.820
Phone? Since when
did you get a phone?

53:47.822 --> 53:50.758
You never told me.
Are you lying to me, man?

53:50.760 --> 53:52.693
- This is some place...
- Why you do that?

53:52.695 --> 53:54.528
- I'm sorry... Very sorry to interrupt.
- Huh?

53:54.530 --> 53:56.296
Oh, no problem.

53:56.298 --> 53:58.032
I was gonna say,
this is some place

53:58.034 --> 54:00.300
you guys got here.
Can we look around?

54:00.302 --> 54:01.938
Yeah, please do.

54:04.572 --> 54:06.407
You told me
one person will show up,

54:06.409 --> 54:08.675
then three people show up
that we don't know.

54:08.677 --> 54:10.911
Why you lie to me?

54:10.913 --> 54:12.780
Look, he's got
a bag of money.

54:12.782 --> 54:15.014
You invite strangers
to this facility,

54:15.016 --> 54:16.883
- you cannot do that.
- I just invited him.

54:16.885 --> 54:18.686
Oh, my God.

54:18.688 --> 54:20.586
- So what? So what?
- He's got the money.

54:20.588 --> 54:22.655
I didn't know three people
were gonna show up. Look...

54:22.657 --> 54:24.590
You lied to me,
and what next?

54:24.592 --> 54:25.925
- You know?
- [Jon] He's a pro,

54:25.927 --> 54:27.228
he's one of the best
in the business.

54:27.230 --> 54:29.595
- How do you know this?
- Because that's what the guys told me.

54:29.597 --> 54:31.030
You're so naive,
I'm sorry to tell you.

54:31.032 --> 54:32.633
You have to learn.
You have to learn.

54:32.635 --> 54:35.635
- Go up to him.
- Before you buy a new phone, you have to learn about life.

54:35.637 --> 54:37.306
- Because you don't know.
- [Jon] Okay.

54:39.742 --> 54:41.541
They're gonna abuse you,
use you.

54:41.543 --> 54:42.976
I'm not focused
on the girls, I...

54:42.978 --> 54:45.445
Yes, you are,
you look at her like stupid.

54:45.447 --> 54:46.780
Just focus
on his bag of money.

54:46.782 --> 54:48.682
- [girls squeal] - [Harvey] What money?
He maybe don't have...

54:48.684 --> 54:49.950
I invited him
because he has money,

54:49.952 --> 54:51.651
I didn't know he would
bring two girls.

54:51.653 --> 54:53.554
- Come on, just pick it up.
- I can't.

54:53.556 --> 54:54.887
You can do it. Come on.

54:54.889 --> 54:56.090
Look at what
she's doing.

54:56.092 --> 54:57.657
When are we ever
in a place like this?

54:57.659 --> 55:00.827
I don't want to be
in a place like this!

55:00.829 --> 55:02.695
- Do it!
- Oh, my God.

55:02.697 --> 55:04.664
What are you doing?
Look at what she's doing.

55:04.666 --> 55:07.434
- It kind of looks like my dad.
- What do you mean, who cares?

55:07.436 --> 55:08.836
Hey, bitch,
what are you doing?

55:08.838 --> 55:12.072
Stop! Stop,
what are you doing?

55:12.074 --> 55:14.141
Don't touch my stuff, okay?

55:14.143 --> 55:15.775
- Hey! Excuse <i>me,</i> don't touch <i>me.</i>
- What are you doing?

55:15.777 --> 55:17.543
[Andrei] Not cool with you
touching my girl.

55:17.545 --> 55:19.045
Yeah.

55:19.047 --> 55:22.682
Any more shit out of you two, I'm gonna
punch you both in your livers, okay?

55:22.684 --> 55:24.952
- [Harvey] Huh.
- Who the fuck is this goblin?

55:24.954 --> 55:26.753
Goblin?

55:26.755 --> 55:30.057
Goblin doesn't like corporate
crooks in his house, okay?

55:30.059 --> 55:33.659
Jon, he works for corporate.
Yeah, you're a spy.

55:33.661 --> 55:35.561
- [scoffs] - You work
for them, right?

55:35.563 --> 55:37.664
- [Jon] No, he...
- You try to come here to test me,

55:37.666 --> 55:39.999
- I bet you. That's what you're gonna do.
- Harvey, he's not a spy.

55:40.001 --> 55:41.068
He just wants
the gold teeth.

55:41.070 --> 55:44.604
- What the fuck are you on?
- I am on anything.

55:44.606 --> 55:47.074
Nothing.
What do you mean "on"?

55:47.076 --> 55:48.608
- Drugs. I don't know.
- I mean...

55:48.610 --> 55:52.679
You come here to my office
and start fight, right?

55:52.681 --> 55:53.813
It's a blackmail, man.

55:53.815 --> 55:53.813
I'm getting real tired
looking at this dude's

55:53.815 --> 55:56.016
face,

55:56.018 --> 55:58.786
so we doing this or not?
I got reservations at Ago.

55:58.788 --> 56:01.889
- Actually we want to go to Nobu.
- In Malibu.

56:01.891 --> 56:04.425
- Nobu, Malibu.
- [Harvey chuckles]

56:04.427 --> 56:07.927
[bags rustle]

56:07.929 --> 56:09.862
[contents rattle]

56:09.864 --> 56:13.967
- You happy?
- Whoa.

56:13.969 --> 56:15.572
You mind if I use
your counter over there?

56:25.880 --> 56:28.417
♪

56:33.556 --> 56:37.023
How the hell did you get
210 ounces of gold teeth here?

56:37.025 --> 56:38.627
Hard work.

56:43.731 --> 56:46.099
You got any more bags
of this stuff?

56:46.101 --> 56:47.737
Yes, we do.

56:54.009 --> 56:55.177
[light switch clicks]

57:30.545 --> 57:32.713
All these boxes
are full of scrap?

57:32.715 --> 57:35.182
What are you, D.B. Cooper
or something?

57:35.184 --> 57:37.217
[Harvey] I work in Chinatown
for many decades

57:37.219 --> 57:38.751
before I start my business.

57:38.753 --> 57:41.220
Normally morgues
throw away teeth,

57:41.222 --> 57:44.590
but I collect as souvenir.
I have all these boxes.

57:44.592 --> 57:46.728
What about that?
[laughs]

57:49.130 --> 57:50.164
[chuckles]

57:50.166 --> 57:52.566
- You know what we're gonna do?
- What?

57:52.568 --> 57:54.767
I think that we can agree
that I'll use this

57:54.769 --> 57:57.170
as a down payment for all
the rest of this shit.

57:57.172 --> 58:00.907
Agree nothing.
How much is in it?

58:00.909 --> 58:04.110
- $125,000.
- Wait a minute, I have to check, okay?

58:04.112 --> 58:06.847
- Go right ahead.
- I don't trust you.

58:06.849 --> 58:09.652
- [zipper opening]
- I don't. Oh.

58:13.621 --> 58:15.524
- Looks like the real thing.
- Mm-hmm.

58:17.159 --> 58:18.891
Oh, yeah, it is.

58:18.893 --> 58:20.496
Okay, cool.

58:23.032 --> 58:25.197
[zipper closes]

58:25.199 --> 58:28.568
You give me a couple months, I
can sell all this scrap for you.

58:28.570 --> 58:30.237
All right? With the
quality you got here,

58:30.239 --> 58:32.773
I am going to make us
a ton of money. A ton.

58:32.775 --> 58:34.941
But I get half
of what we sell,

58:34.943 --> 58:36.142
and I would ask
that you don't tell

58:36.144 --> 58:38.345
any of the other refineries
about what your stash here.

58:38.347 --> 58:41.715
Look, there will be always
competition in business, my friend.

58:41.717 --> 58:42.883
And you don't know that?

58:42.885 --> 58:45.719
And you are not the only
salesperson in the entire world.

58:45.721 --> 58:48.688
You think you own
the world? Huh?

58:48.690 --> 58:50.090
But anyway, you know what?

58:50.092 --> 58:52.693
I suspect you are
a spy, corporate spy.

58:52.695 --> 58:55.162
Let's just start it tonight,
like little arrangement here,

58:55.164 --> 58:57.798
and we'll see what happen,
where it goes.

58:57.800 --> 58:59.666
Okay?

58:59.668 --> 59:03.003
Can we do that?

59:03.005 --> 59:06.706
Jon, I don't know
where you dug this guy up,

59:06.708 --> 59:09.376
but let's just make sure this is
profitable for you and I, okay?

59:09.378 --> 59:11.878
Hey, dude, I'm here.
Why you even talk to him?

59:11.880 --> 59:14.347
He's not in charge.
I am in charge.

59:14.349 --> 59:16.286
Okay? I'm watching you!

59:18.052 --> 59:19.353
Anyhow...

59:19.355 --> 59:21.354
- [latches close]
- I have to go now.

59:21.356 --> 59:23.789
I'm tired. Come on,
let's go. Let's go.

59:23.791 --> 59:25.291
Come on, watch your head.

59:25.293 --> 59:26.328
[light switch clicks]

59:28.630 --> 59:30.697
Well, I did not expect this.

59:30.699 --> 59:32.264
- I give you a little credit.
- I told you.

59:32.266 --> 59:34.668
I wouldn't have brought you
into this if it wasn't legit.

59:34.670 --> 59:37.170
Yeah, but I need
my keys back anyhow.

59:37.172 --> 59:40.072
I need the keys,
come on.

59:40.074 --> 59:42.409
I'm just going to take a little
bit of money, we'll figure out...

59:42.411 --> 59:44.144
No, you cannot take this money.
We have...

59:44.146 --> 59:46.412
First of all, was it a test?
Maybe it was the FBI,

59:46.414 --> 59:49.249
or this guy
maybe was undercover,

59:49.251 --> 59:51.851
guy from the cremation
foundation, okay?

59:51.853 --> 59:53.954
- You cannot just take it.
- That doesn't make any sense.

59:53.956 --> 59:54.921
I need a place to live.

59:54.923 --> 59:56.923
Traci's already asking me
what I'm doing.

59:56.925 --> 59:58.258
I don't have money,
I have nothing.

59:58.260 --> 59:59.793
Traci will love you
without money,

59:59.795 --> 01:00:02.061
that will be great test
for you guys.

01:00:02.063 --> 01:00:04.764
- Okay, help me with this, come on.
- Well...

01:00:04.766 --> 01:00:07.133
Let me tell you, I take
good care of this, okay?

01:00:07.135 --> 01:00:08.501
You cannot spend it.

01:00:08.503 --> 01:00:11.304
- Okay? So help me with this, come on.
- Where are we gonna...

01:00:11.306 --> 01:00:13.005
- Hold this bag.
- Where are we gonna hide it?

01:00:13.007 --> 01:00:14.840
In my place.
I know where we hide it.

01:00:14.842 --> 01:00:16.742
- Very special place.
- [zipper closes]

01:00:16.744 --> 01:00:18.047
Help me.
Come on, let's go.

01:00:29.791 --> 01:00:34.026
- Okay, we are here.
- [bag thuds]

01:00:34.028 --> 01:00:35.632
Hold it.

01:00:41.070 --> 01:00:42.672
Okay, open it.

01:00:45.440 --> 01:00:46.708
Follow me.

01:00:49.777 --> 01:00:51.711
- Okay, hold this.
- Yeah.

01:00:51.713 --> 01:00:55.014
This is great place to store
money, you don't think?

01:00:55.016 --> 01:00:57.316
Hey, dude, nobody
will expect it.

01:00:57.318 --> 01:00:59.786
Where the hell did you
get an ATM machine?

01:00:59.788 --> 01:01:01.420
I have resources, okay?

01:01:01.422 --> 01:01:03.757
This is antique,
this is collector's item.

01:01:03.759 --> 01:01:05.124
Beautiful, huh?

01:01:05.126 --> 01:01:08.028
Okay, now listen, we cannot do
business right here. Attend business.

01:01:08.030 --> 01:01:10.764
- You know why?
- Why?

01:01:10.766 --> 01:01:13.900
Because this is our club.
That's why, okay?

01:01:13.902 --> 01:01:16.369
- And nobody comes here except us.
- Okay.

01:01:16.371 --> 01:01:18.804
- No-no spending, okay?
- Yeah.

01:01:18.806 --> 01:01:21.007
Trust me, friendship
before money.

01:01:21.009 --> 01:01:24.211
Understand?
Can you say this?

01:01:24.213 --> 01:01:25.412
- Yeah.
- What?

01:01:25.414 --> 01:01:28.248
- Trust me, friendship before money. Yeah.
- Right!

01:01:28.250 --> 01:01:31.418
[keypad beeping]

01:01:31.420 --> 01:01:33.690
[door groans]

01:01:51.806 --> 01:01:57.110
[thunderclap]

01:01:57.112 --> 01:01:59.278
<i>Startling...</i>

01:01:59.280 --> 01:02:04.219
<i>because they seem
new, sudden.</i>

01:02:06.221 --> 01:02:10.090
<i>But most are not new</i>

01:02:10.092 --> 01:02:13.092
<i>to the signs of the ages.</i>

01:02:13.094 --> 01:02:15.427
♪

01:02:15.429 --> 01:02:18.465
Wow, what an ending.
You know, I never thought

01:02:18.467 --> 01:02:21.233
I would enjoy watching these
black and white movies so much.

01:02:21.235 --> 01:02:22.802
See? I told you
you'd like it.

01:02:22.804 --> 01:02:26.539
It's my favorite thing to do on my days
off, watch black and white movies.

01:02:26.541 --> 01:02:28.374
[chuckles]

01:02:28.376 --> 01:02:30.309
And I don't know who came
up with these plots,

01:02:30.311 --> 01:02:32.579
but it's as if the last
10 minutes

01:02:32.581 --> 01:02:34.847
are all about
trusting no one.

01:02:34.849 --> 01:02:37.150
[chuckles]

01:02:37.152 --> 01:02:39.084
How about we have a date
night at your place?

01:02:39.086 --> 01:02:41.521
We can order a big thing
of pizza, some wine,

01:02:41.523 --> 01:02:44.990
- and <i>Double Indemnity?</i>
- Yeah, yeah.

01:02:44.992 --> 01:02:46.959
- Sounds-sounds perfect.
- Yeah?

01:02:46.961 --> 01:02:51.197
My-my place won't be ready
for a few weeks, though, so...

01:02:51.199 --> 01:02:53.934
What, you got a condo in the
Palisades or something?

01:02:53.936 --> 01:02:56.336
Uh... working on it.

01:02:56.338 --> 01:02:59.940
Well, you're more than welcome
to stay here until then.

01:02:59.942 --> 01:03:03.478
Yeah?
Cool, yeah.

01:03:07.048 --> 01:03:09.384
♪

01:03:26.902 --> 01:03:30.202
- [door squeaks] - All
right, boys, all right.

01:03:30.204 --> 01:03:32.037
- [Harvey] Hey.
- How we doin'? How you doin'?

01:03:32.039 --> 01:03:35.242
Okay, this map right here
details all the drop points.

01:03:35.244 --> 01:03:38.612
Okay? All the deals
go down after 8:00,

01:03:38.614 --> 01:03:41.081
you're gonna tally
all your deals in this.

01:03:41.083 --> 01:03:43.282
No problem,
I'm good organizer.

01:03:43.284 --> 01:03:44.751
[Andrei] Excellent.

01:03:44.753 --> 01:03:47.920
Tomorrow night, your first drop is
gonna be the San Marino location.

01:03:47.922 --> 01:03:50.222
I want you to wait
for a guy named Twigs.

01:03:50.224 --> 01:03:53.559
He's like... he's a funny
looking dude in a hat, okay?

01:03:53.561 --> 01:03:55.427
- Who?
- Twigs.

01:03:55.429 --> 01:03:57.530
Jon, we need bodyguard.

01:03:57.532 --> 01:04:01.367
- Yeah, if we dealing with gangsters?
- [Andrei] Listen.

01:04:01.369 --> 01:04:04.271
My guys are, like, tech
nerds and dentists.

01:04:04.273 --> 01:04:07.407
Worse that's gonna happen is, they're
gonna throw some dental floss on you.

01:04:07.409 --> 01:04:09.409
[laughs]
Are you kidding me?

01:04:09.411 --> 01:04:10.577
Listen to me,
I don't want you

01:04:10.579 --> 01:04:11.644
messing with my dudes,
all right?

01:04:11.646 --> 01:04:14.481
Wait a minute, we are here
to make money, all right?

01:04:14.483 --> 01:04:17.150
And I am businessman.
You understand that?

01:04:17.152 --> 01:04:19.251
- Yeah.
- We have to be on the same page, right?

01:04:19.253 --> 01:04:21.054
We're on the same page.
Now we're talkin'.

01:04:21.056 --> 01:04:23.657
Now we're talkin',
all right. Very good.

01:04:23.659 --> 01:04:25.592
I'll see you jokesters
in a couple weeks.

01:04:25.594 --> 01:04:27.693
Hopefully by then we're
gonna be making some dough.

01:04:27.695 --> 01:04:29.362
We'll see.

01:04:29.364 --> 01:04:31.597
- Happy scrapping, boys.
- All right.

01:04:31.599 --> 01:04:34.434
[door whines]

01:04:34.436 --> 01:04:36.972
♪

01:07:52.134 --> 01:07:54.666
- Morning.
- Hey.

01:07:54.668 --> 01:07:56.401
You wanna get up?

01:07:56.403 --> 01:07:57.670
I have a really
awesome place

01:07:57.672 --> 01:07:59.238
I wanna take you
for breakfast.

01:07:59.240 --> 01:08:01.240
Yeah, let's do it.

01:08:01.242 --> 01:08:04.209
But you gotta get up.

01:08:04.211 --> 01:08:06.713
- 10 more minutes?
- [chuckles]

01:08:06.715 --> 01:08:09.349
All right, I'm gonna
go get ready.

01:08:09.351 --> 01:08:11.784
By the time I get back,
you better be up.

01:08:11.786 --> 01:08:13.688
Okay. Promise.

01:08:58.966 --> 01:09:02.434
- What the hell's this?
- Oh, shit.

01:09:02.435 --> 01:09:04.536
Um, yeah, uh...

01:09:04.537 --> 01:09:07.674
[stammers]
I-I can explain, um...

01:09:07.676 --> 01:09:09.975
I-I-I-I work with a friend
of mine, he runs a morgue,

01:09:09.978 --> 01:09:11.710
and I help out there,
so we...

01:09:11.712 --> 01:09:14.413
- Wait, a morgue?
- Yeah, a morgue, um...

01:09:14.416 --> 01:09:16.515
Part of his gig
is putting masks

01:09:16.518 --> 01:09:20.620
on, um, disfigured people's
faces for funerals.

01:09:20.622 --> 01:09:21.854
I know it's-it's weird.

01:09:21.856 --> 01:09:25.558
Um, and-and he made a mask
of my face for some reason,

01:09:25.560 --> 01:09:28.760
and it... honestly, it's
harmless, there's nothing to it.

01:09:28.761 --> 01:09:29.895
Well, you said you were...
Wait...

01:09:29.898 --> 01:09:32.397
No, no, no, you said you were
in the gold business.

01:09:32.399 --> 01:09:33.832
Yeah. I am, yeah, exactly.

01:09:33.835 --> 01:09:36.001
I am in the gold business,
and Harvey,

01:09:36.002 --> 01:09:39.339
that's my friend's name,
he's got boxes of gold teeth,

01:09:39.341 --> 01:09:41.273
and we're setting up
this business,

01:09:41.274 --> 01:09:43.009
and I just didn't know
how to tell you, I...

01:09:43.011 --> 01:09:44.544
Do you even
have your own place?

01:09:44.546 --> 01:09:46.379
We can't spend the money
right now,

01:09:46.381 --> 01:09:49.281
and I was supposed to get
a place a couple weeks ago.

01:09:49.283 --> 01:09:50.683
I'm working on it.
I know it's weird,

01:09:50.685 --> 01:09:51.984
we've just been
getting along so well...

01:09:51.987 --> 01:09:53.719
So I-i-is it illegal?

01:09:53.720 --> 01:09:56.755
No, no, no, no, not at all.
It's not illegal. Look, I...

01:09:56.757 --> 01:09:58.691
Okay, why don't you come
see where I work?

01:09:58.693 --> 01:10:01.027
Why don't you meet my friend
and it'll make sense?

01:10:01.029 --> 01:10:04.363
I know it's weird to see
a mask and teeth and shit,

01:10:04.365 --> 01:10:06.799
but it's... it...
it all adds up.

01:10:06.801 --> 01:10:07.799
Trust me, it's harmless.

01:10:07.801 --> 01:10:10.836
Why am I just hearing
about this friend now?

01:10:10.838 --> 01:10:13.906
You know since we first met,
you have been so secretive.

01:10:13.908 --> 01:10:15.775
Please just give me
a second chance.

01:10:15.777 --> 01:10:18.777
I got nothing to hide,
I'll take you to him.

01:10:18.779 --> 01:10:21.281
Whatever you want to know,
I'll show you.

01:10:21.283 --> 01:10:23.752
[stammers] Is that cool?

01:10:25.953 --> 01:10:29.421
- Just give me a chance. It's...
- Whatever.

01:10:29.423 --> 01:10:31.327
Fuck...

